                  travelgirlaug18
                  Escondido, California
                  53
                  Reviewed November 28, 2014
                  Missed the Mark

                  First off, I know this is an extended stay property so I did not expect much. With that being said The staff did work hard at trying to rectify our stay however it still was not what I would consider a very comfortable stay. For being an extended stay place, they strip the room down to the bare bones. They dont even leave you a hair dryer. So basically you have to go the front desk and ask fo dishes, cups, coffee maker, hair dryer, silverware, pots ,pans whatever. Also word to the wish dont book your room here through booking .com. They have a ton of ridiculous polices when it comes to booking that were not reserved directly from them. it was a major hassle. Our first room was freezing cold, and the heating/ac unit was falling apart . it took forever to heat up and once it did, it was blowing so much wet, dusty smoky air into the room that my poor mom started having an asthma attack. We left that room and returned the front desk saying we needed another room or to be refunded because my mom was on the verge of having to be checked into a hospital for a breathing treatment. They were going to refund us but I had to log into booking.com first and cancel my reservation even though i paid the hotel directly before they could process our refund. While i was trying to get that done, the desk clerk who was very nice and seemed concerned about my moms health found us another room with an upgraded heating system . I checked it out and it worked for what we needed. All in all the stay ended up being just ok but it was a hassle. I think next time I'll stick to my marriots .

                  Room tip: Ask for a room with an upgraded a/c unit. Book directly. Try to avoid an online booking website like expedia, booking.com... etc.
                  Date of stay: November 2014

                  Reviewed November 23, 2014
                  Sad

                  This property is depressing which is sad really. It is located in the midst of a bunch of medical buildings and hospitals. They bill it as a place to stay when your loved one is in the hospital. Staying at Extended Stay America will only depress loved ones further than they already are. My room was dank, dark and felt old and dirty. Absolutely nothing but towels and a made bed came with the room. I had to "place an order" for a coffee pot, utensils and a coffee mug for my room. They insisted on delivering it...and after three hours they did. I had to wait to nuke my dinner until they got around to making their delivery. Ah yes, the microwave - think it is an original model...my frozen dinner said to cook on high for 8 minutes - I did - it was still frozen. Took about 20 minutes to cook. If you enjoy no maid service (unless you pay extra), taking out your own garbage and making your own bed for the same price as a hotel whose rooms come with maid service AND a coffee pot this is the place for you.
